Many people are trapped beneath the rubble of a four-storey building which collapsed around 1.30pm in the Jabi area of Abuja on Friday. Eye witness at the scene of the accident reported that the building which was under construction when it collapsed had close to thirty people inside. Acting President Yemi Osinbajo visited the site of the four-storey buildingÂ with senior government officials, including the FCT Minister, Mohammed Bello; and Secretary to Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha. As at the time of writing this, rescue officials were said to have rescued about nine persons while two corpses were evacuated. It was believed that the heavy downpour affected the success of the rescue operations. 